    {
      "id": "edge-classes-note-audit-surface",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Current Edge Surface",
      "position": {
        "x": 40,
        "y": 980
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Current Edge Surface\n\nObserved current edge semantics:\n\n- many graphs still use plain `reference` edges\n- some graphs also use typed edge names like `relates`, `flows-to`, `dataFlow`, `hierarchy`, `child`, and `peer`\n- a lot of practical meaning currently lives in the edge `label`\n- rendering is carried ad hoc in edge `style` fields such as `stroke`, `strokeWidth`, and `dash`\n- graph-level defaults still come from document settings like `defaultEdgeColor` and `edgeRouting`",
        "_classBinding": {
